Title: Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642) contains a total of 190 point data values acquired at a spacing between 100 and 1000 metres. The data is located in QLD and were acquired in 1996, under project No. 199642 for BHP Group Ltd.

Lineage: This Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642) survey acquired for BHP Group Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 190 point data values. The data is located in QLD and were acquired in 1996. The point located data were collected in irregular grids layout at a station spacing between 100 and 1000 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.
SourceDescription: This Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Hazel Creek Gravity Survey, Qld (P199642) survey acquired for BHP Group Ltd.

This dataset contains a total of 179 point data values. The data is located in WA and were acquired in 1997. The point located data were collected in grid layout at a station spacing between 1000 and 4000 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. Lineage: This Heathcote Naganbie 1:100,000 In-fill (P199738), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Heathcote Naganbie 1:100,000 In-fill (P199738) survey acquired for None. This dataset contains a total of 1767 point data values. The data is located in VIC and were acquired in 1997. The point located data were collected in irregular layout at a station spacing between 250 and 500 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.

Title: Kaniva Infill (P199631), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Kaniva Infill (P199631) contains a total of 586 point data values acquired at a spacing of 5000 metres. The data is located in VIC and were acquired in 1996, under project No. 199631 for None.
